Salt & Pepper Grill has long been our family’s favorite place to order Indian food from. It’s been a few months since we last ordered, and tonight we ordered delivery straight from their website. Cheaper than ordering from a third-party like DoorDash and hopefully they get more/all of the money that way. Our confirmation said it would be 55 minutes—so our hungry household was pleasantly surprised when it arrived in under 20! Drop-off was contactless. Everything was SO DELICIOUS, as usual. All of their veggie options are SO good. This time around we also got an order of Fish Pakora Tilapia...loved it! Highly recommend Salt & Pepper Grill!!

Best rated Indian food in DC? Yes, please. With high expectations, my wife and two friends ventured up to NW DC from Capitol Hill to try this place's naan and tikka masala. My friend and I had it in our minds that this place would be a nice sit down restaurant so we were surprised to find a whole-in-the-wall restaurant with fluorescent lighting.  You order your food next to a buffet of Indian food, which doesn't give you the best impression, but wait until you get the food. The naan is for sure the best I've had in DC perfectly hot and buttered. I loved the tikka masala, but it was a little more sweet than you are probably used to (My wife and friend didn't enjoy it, but I loved it!). My wife and friend got the biryani and enjoyed it. My other friend (from Delaware) got butter chicken and enjoyed it too.  If you like Indian, venture up to NW to at least try this place.

Basic.  That's the word.  The food is basic.  Nothing fancy.  No fancy plates.  Just good food.  It's to the point.  It's quality.  Just sauce.  Just meat.  And your mouth.  It's service is basic.   No fancy uniforms.  No attitude.  No Bull$H!+.  Just a plain smile.  The decor is basic.  The signs look handmade.  The lights don't match.  It looks like the last store that was here was looted in a riot, and this place just set up shop and start serving food.  It's basically cheap.  For the amount of food that you get, you really can't complain at all.  Oh, and if you bring in a Howard University ID, they give you $1 off your food.
